.TH "drm_vblank_init" 9 "drm_vblank_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_vblank_init \- initialize vblank support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_vblank_init
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_crtcs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "num_crtcs" 12
number of CRTCs supported by \fIdev\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function initializes vblank support for \fInum_crtcs\fP display pipelines.
Cleanup is handled automatically through a cleanup function added with
\fBdrmm_add_action_or_reset\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success or a negative error code on failure.
